        <p class="isSelectedEnd"><span>Dear Sir,</span></p>
        <p><span>Please find below the IST review questions along with
            our responses for the Sale Order (Domestic Sales) module in
            SPINRISE ERP.</span></p>
        <h3 data-section-id="ro1tpx" data-start="226" data-end="258"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="230" data-end="258">1.
              Credit Limit Override</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="260" data-end="421"><strong data-start="260"
            data-end="273">Question:</strong><br data-start="273"
            data-end="276">
          Who is permitted to override a credit limit breach and save
          the order? Is this controlled by user level (ulevel) or a
          separate approval workflow?</p>
        <p data-start="423" data-end="703"><strong data-start="423"
            data-end="434">Answer:</strong><br data-start="434"
            data-end="437">
          Credit limit override must <strong data-start="464"
            data-end="497">not be permitted to all users</strong>. It
          should be controlled through a <strong data-start="533"
            data-end="565">role-based approval workflow</strong>, rather
          than relying only on user level (ulevel). Only authorized
          users (e.g., Sales Manager / Finance) should have override
          permissions.</p>
        <hr data-start="705" data-end="708">
        <h3 data-section-id="1qrq0k1" data-start="710" data-end="743"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="714" data-end="743">2. Agent
              Code Requirement</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="745" data-end="878"><strong data-start="745"
            data-end="758">Question:</strong><br data-start="758"
            data-end="761">
          Is the Agent Code requirement company-wide or configurable per
          division? Which parameter / setup table controls this?</p>
        <p data-start="880" data-end="1165"><strong data-start="880"
            data-end="891">Answer:</strong><br data-start="891"
            data-end="894">
          Currently, the Agent Code requirement is <strong
            data-start="935" data-end="982">not configured at company or
            division level</strong>. It is controlled based on <strong
            data-start="1010" data-end="1038">Party Type configuration</strong>
          (e.g., D1, D2, D5, etc.). However, it is recommended to make
          this <strong data-start="1105" data-end="1141">configurable
            via parameter setup</strong> for better flexibility.</p>
        <hr data-start="1167" data-end="1170">
        <h3 data-section-id="xcekmz" data-start="1172" data-end="1213"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="1176" data-end="1213">3.
              Offer Rate Flag (OfferRateFlg)</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="1215" data-end="1359"><strong data-start="1215"
            data-end="1228">Question:</strong><br data-start="1228"
            data-end="1231">
          What business condition triggers OfferRateFlg = True? Is this
          a system parameter, user preference, or customer-specific
          setting?</p>
        <p data-start="1361" data-end="1504"><strong data-start="1361"
            data-end="1372">Answer:</strong><br data-start="1372"
            data-end="1375">
          OfferRateFlg should be controlled as a <strong
            data-start="1414" data-end="1434">system parameter</strong>,
          with the option to allow <strong data-start="1461"
            data-end="1488">customer-level override</strong> where
          required.</p>
        <hr data-start="1506" data-end="1509">
        <h3 data-section-id="b4uk8v" data-start="1511" data-end="1537"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="1515" data-end="1537">4. CSM
              Integration</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="1539" data-end="1687"><strong data-start="1539"
            data-end="1552">Question:</strong><br data-start="1552"
            data-end="1555">
          What is the endpoint, authentication method, and payload
          structure for the CSM external system (apiUrl)? Is this live
          in production?</p>
        <p data-start="1689" data-end="1930"><strong data-start="1689"
            data-end="1700">Answer:</strong><br data-start="1700"
            data-end="1703">
          CSM integration should be implemented using a <strong
            data-start="1749" data-end="1770">standard REST API</strong>,
          with proper <strong data-start="1784" data-end="1822">authentication
            (e.g., token-based)</strong> and a <strong
            data-start="1829" data-end="1856">structured JSON payload</strong>.
          This needs to be clearly defined and validated for production
          readiness.</p>
        <hr data-start="1932" data-end="1935">
        <h3 data-section-id="1tbht66" data-start="1937" data-end="1961"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="1941" data-end="1961">5. TCS
              Threshold</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="1963" data-end="2061"><strong data-start="1963"
            data-end="1976">Question:</strong><br data-start="1976"
            data-end="1979">
          What is the current TCS threshold amount? Is this stored in a
          table or hard-coded?</p>
        <p data-start="2063" data-end="2211"><strong data-start="2063"
            data-end="2074">Answer:</strong><br data-start="2074"
            data-end="2077">
          The TCS threshold should be stored in a <strong
            data-start="2117" data-end="2150">parameter/configuration
            table</strong> and maintained dynamically. It should <strong
            data-start="2189" data-end="2210">not be hard-coded</strong>.</p>
        <hr data-start="2213" data-end="2216">
        <h3 data-section-id="1mldese" data-start="2218" data-end="2244"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="2222" data-end="2244">6. Mix
              Ratio Rules</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="2246" data-end="2397"><strong data-start="2246"
            data-end="2259">Question:</strong><br data-start="2259"
            data-end="2262">
          Are there contract types other than JW that require Mix Ratio
          %? Are there other contract-type-specific rules not visible in
          this form?</p>
        <p data-start="2399" data-end="2625"><strong data-start="2399"
            data-end="2410">Answer:</strong><br data-start="2410"
            data-end="2413">
          Currently, Mix Ratio % is applicable <strong
            data-start="2450" data-end="2490">only for JW (Job Work)
            contract type</strong>. However, the system should be
          designed to support <strong data-start="2542" data-end="2602">other
            contract types through a configurable rules engine</strong>
          if required in future.</p>
        <hr data-start="2627" data-end="2630">
        <h3 data-section-id="18rmu38" data-start="2632" data-end="2683"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="2636" data-end="2683">7.
              IG_INSBODT vs IG_BODT (Dispatch Process)</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="2685" data-end="2813"><strong data-start="2685"
            data-end="2698">Question:</strong><br data-start="2698"
            data-end="2701">
          What is the business difference between IG_INSBODT and IG_BODT
          for partial dispatch tracking? When is each used?</p>
        <p data-start="2815" data-end="2828"><strong data-start="2815"
            data-end="2826">Answer:</strong></p>
        <ul data-start="2829" data-end="3284">
          <li data-section-id="1aa2ktb" data-start="2829"
            data-end="3054"> <strong data-start="2831" data-end="2846">IG_INSBODT:</strong><br
              data-start="2846" data-end="2849">
            Used for <strong data-start="2860" data-end="2898">Despatch
              Instruction-based process</strong>, where dispatch is
            initiated through an <strong data-start="2939"
              data-end="2963">internal instruction</strong> from
            Sales/Planning to Stores/Dispatch. This flow is <strong
              data-start="3017" data-end="3053">controlled by parameter
              settings</strong>. </li>
          <li data-section-id="1x2a6wb" data-start="3056"
            data-end="3284"> <strong data-start="3058" data-end="3070">IG_BODT:</strong><br
              data-start="3070" data-end="3073">
            Used for <strong data-start="3084" data-end="3110">Direct
              Despatch Advice</strong>, where dispatch is made <strong
              data-start="3135" data-end="3170">directly against the
              Sale Order</strong>, skipping the Despatch Instruction
            stage. This depends on <strong data-start="3229"
              data-end="3283">customer-specific or business process
              requirements</strong>. </li>
        </ul>
        <hr data-start="3286" data-end="3289">
        <h3 data-section-id="wn8o2z" data-start="3291" data-end="3338"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="3295" data-end="3338">8.
              Rate Decimal Precision (RateDeciPos)</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="3340" data-end="3447"><strong data-start="3340"
            data-end="3353">Question:</strong><br data-start="3353"
            data-end="3356">
          What is the standard value of RateDeciPos? Do different
          divisions use different precisions?</p>
        <p data-start="3449" data-end="3610"><strong data-start="3449"
            data-end="3460">Answer:</strong><br data-start="3460"
            data-end="3463">
          RateDeciPos should be <strong data-start="3485"
            data-end="3523">configurable at the division level</strong>,
          typically ranging from <strong data-start="3548"
            data-end="3573">2 to 4 decimal places</strong>, depending on
          business requirements.</p>
        <hr data-start="3612" data-end="3615">
        <h3 data-section-id="16odi2z" data-start="3617" data-end="3666"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="3621" data-end="3666">9.
              Deletion vs Cancellation of Sale Order</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="3668" data-end="3810"><strong data-start="3668"
            data-end="3681">Question:</strong><br data-start="3681"
            data-end="3684">
          Is there ever a requirement to physically delete a sale order,
          or is cancellation (CANCELLED='Y') always sufficient for
          audit?</p>
        <p data-start="3812" data-end="3825"><strong data-start="3812"
            data-end="3823">Answer:</strong></p>
        <ul data-start="3826" data-end="4091">
          <li data-section-id="tq7hji" data-start="3826" data-end="3977">
            <strong data-start="3828" data-end="3840">Deletion</strong> should
            be allowed <strong data-start="3856" data-end="3891">only
              if no further transactions</strong> (dispatch, invoice,
            etc.) have been performed, as part of internal process
            control. </li>
          <li data-section-id="1yvulo3" data-start="3978"
            data-end="4091"> Once the order is processed, <strong
              data-start="4009" data-end="4058">cancellation (CANCELLED
              = 'Y') should be used</strong> to ensure proper audit
            tracking. </li>
        </ul>
        <hr data-start="4093" data-end="4096">
        <h3 data-section-id="1cgo8nu" data-start="4098" data-end="4152"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="4102" data-end="4152">10.
              Report Footer Configuration (fr_RepFooter)</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="4154" data-end="4255"><strong data-start="4154"
            data-end="4167">Question:</strong><br data-start="4167"
            data-end="4170">
          What does fr_RepFooter configure? Are there footer variants
          per customer or division?</p>
        <p data-start="4257" data-end="4419"><strong data-start="4257"
            data-end="4268">Answer:</strong><br data-start="4268"
            data-end="4271">
          fr_RepFooter is used to configure <strong data-start="4305"
            data-end="4330">report footer details</strong>, which are
          maintained <strong data-start="4353" data-end="4370">division-wise</strong></p>
        <hr data-start="4421" data-end="4424">
        <h3 data-section-id="1fmqnu8" data-start="4426" data-end="4463"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="4430" data-end="4463">11.
              Multi-Division Sale Order</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="4465" data-end="4572"><strong data-start="4465"
            data-end="4478">Question:</strong><br data-start="4478"
            data-end="4481">
          Can a single sale order span multiple divisions, or is each
          order always division-specific?</p>
        <p data-start="4574" data-end="4680"><strong data-start="4574"
            data-end="4585">Answer:</strong><br data-start="4585"
            data-end="4588">
          A sale order is <strong data-start="4604" data-end="4632">always
            division-specific</strong>. A single order cannot span
          multiple divisions.</p>
        <hr data-start="4682" data-end="4685">
        <h3 data-section-id="37238k" data-start="4687" data-end="4731"><span
            role="text"><strong data-start="4691" data-end="4731">12.
              Auto-Mail System (CheckAutoMail)</strong></span></h3>
        <p data-start="4733" data-end="4839"><strong data-start="4733"
            data-end="4746">Question:</strong><br data-start="4746"
            data-end="4749">
          What email system is used for CheckAutoMail? SMTP or
          third-party? What triggers auto-mail?</p>
        <p data-start="4841" data-end="5093"><strong data-start="4841"
            data-end="4852">Answer:</strong><br data-start="4852"
            data-end="4855">
          Auto-mail functionality currently uses an <strong
            data-start="4897" data-end="4926">SMTP server configuration</strong>.
          Integration with <strong data-start="4945" data-end="4975">third-party
            email services</strong> can also be implemented if required.
          Auto-mail is typically triggered during <strong
            data-start="5053" data-end="5092">print or order
            confirmation process</strong>.</p>
        <p>This is for your kind information</p>
