          <p>Dear Annamalai and Seenivasan,<br>
            <br>
            I have reviewed both the 2 April and the 10 April versions
            of the Sales Order FSD from the QA mail ID. I want to give
            both of you a clear picture of what has improved, what still
            needs to be done, and what each of you must action before
            this document can proceed.<br>
            <br>
            <b>On the improvement from version 1 to version 2 —
              Annamalai</b><br>
            <br>
            <b>This is a substantial revision and the effort is visible.</b>
            Between 2 April and today, ten sections that were either
            absent or inadequate have been brought to a proper standard.
            Let me be specific.<br>
            <br>
            Section 3 (Field Rules) is new and covers 25 fields with
            mandatory flags, data types, lengths, defaults, and notes.
            Section 4 (Validation Rules) is now correctly structured
            into four categories — Pre-Add, Header, Line Entry, and
            Customer-Specific — with error messages inline. This was
            entirely absent in version 1. Section 6 (TC Framework) is
            now present and correctly states that the Sale Order form
            does not trigger stock movements or accounting entries at
            the point of order creation — TC activation happens
            downstream at despatch and invoice. This is the correct
            understanding and it protects the SPINRISE developer from
            building the wrong integration point.<br>
            <br>
            Section 7 (Common Module Dependencies) now analyses
            Spinmod.bas, modGeneral.bas, and clsCrystal.cls at the
            function level. Section 8 (DB Operations) now documents both
            KSP_LSALES_SALEORDER and KSP_TCSAmountCheckLSales with their
            business rules. Section 9 (Error Messages) is entirely new —
            39 exact messages with trigger conditions. Sections 12
            (SPINRISE Recommendations), 13 (IST Review Questions), and
            14 (Summary Scorecard) are all new additions. This is a
            complete restructuring of the document and it is aligned
