            ig_param flag-driven behaviour? If not, Stage 0 is not
            complete for this form. SPINRISE cannot be built from a form
            that still contains hardcoded customer ID checks.<br>
            <br>
            <b>3. Three stored procedures require code submission and
              Follow-up Prompt B analysis.</b><br>
            Section 8.4 documents KSP_LSALES_SALEORDER and Section 8.5
            documents KSP_TCSAmountCheckLSales at a business-rule
            description level. Section 5.5 references a third SP,
            Ksp_PendingOrderVal, used in the credit limit calculation.
            None of the three have been analysed from the actual SQL
            code. The rate calculation inside KSP_LSALES_SALEORDER, the
            union logic and threshold comparison inside
            KSP_TCSAmountCheckLSales, and the pending order value query
            inside Ksp_PendingOrderVal must all be submitted to Claude
            using Follow-up Prompt B from the v2 guide. The SP analysis
            must come from the code, not from a description of what the
            SP is intended to do. Please obtain all three SP codes from
            SQL Server Management Studio and run Follow-up Prompt B on
            each.<br>
            <br>
