            Section 8.3, with the field mapping.<br>
            <br>
            <b>5. The document number race condition must be flagged as
              a Critical Defect.</b><br>
            Section 12 Recommendation 4 correctly identifies that
            IG_DOCCONTROL document numbering should be replaced with a
            sequence service. But the underlying risk is not stated as a
            defect. The current code reads MAX+1 from IG_DOCCONTROL
            without a lock, which means concurrent saves from two users
            can produce duplicate order numbers. The RMI PO FSD
            correctly flagged this as CD-2 with an explicit SPINRISE
            fix. Please add this as a Critical Defect entry — the same
            pattern exists here and the same UPDLOCK-based sequence fix
            applies.<br>
            <br>
            <b>6. Section 11 needs SPINRISE configuration flag names and
              defaults.</b><br>
